[2026-03-18T17:38:39.109Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016dU9uHM6jeTYwem7nY66PT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`eventProcessor.ts`** — Added a `nudge()` method to `EventProcessorHandle` that schedules an immediate tick via `setImmediate`, coalesced so multiple rapid-fire nudges collapse into a single tick. The tick body was extracted into `runTick()` shared by both the nudge and the backstop interval.\n\n**`httpApi.ts`** — Added optional `onEventPublished` callback parameter. Called after each of the 3 `publishEvent()` sites (POST events, webhooks, GitLab webhook).\n\n**`triggerScheduler.ts`** — Added optional `onEventPublished` callback parameter, threaded through to `triggerSchedulerTick()`, called after each `publishEvent()`.\n\n**`index.ts`** — Wired `eventProcessor.nudge` as the callback to both `createHttpApi` and `startTriggerScheduler`. Increased the backstop interval from **2s to 30s** since the nudge now handles the fast path.\n\n**Net effect**: Events are processed within a single `setImmediate` tick (~1ms) instead of up to 2 seconds. Idle DB polling is reduced from every 2s to every 30s. The interval remains as a safety net for deferred/retried events."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":309,"cache_read_input_tokens":59362,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":309},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"593dcb05-04b8-4463-b769-cc9d945e1617","uuid":"0217e477-bd99-4d4b-bb45-3972faaf24b4"}
